    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cf0d8c6d_f4413fe1",
        "filename": "include/core/SkSurfaceProps.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-22T19:57:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So currently (most of) the SkSurface constructors take SkSurfaceProps* so that one can pass in nullptr to mean \u0027use the globals\u0027, which arguably wasn\u0027t needed, it could have taken a SkSurfaceProps\u0026 and required the user to call SkSurfaceProps(kLegacyFontHost_InitType) to create a temporary to pass in (since that\u0027s what is happening when passing nullptr anyway).\n\nIf we remove the Skia globals then either the SkSurface constructors continue to take SkSurfaceProps* and nullptr means \u0027Default\u0027 (no flags unknown/flat pixel geometry) instead, or the SkSurface constructors would be migrated to take SkSurfaceProps\u0026 and one could pass \u0027SkSurfaceProps()\u0027. I suppose what I\u0027m getting at here is that we only need this \u0027Default\u0027 thing because we want a pointer and not a reference (and want to avoid as_lvalue or forcing a name to make an lvalue just so we can take the address of the thing).\n\nIn any even I think it\u0027s probably nicer to just have this return \u0027const SkSurfaceProps\u0026\u0027 and let the callers take the address of it. Even though that\u0027s an extra bit at each use site, it points out that the SkSurface constructors are a little weird.\n\nAlso, it would be really nice if this were all constexpr.",
      "revId": "19bf7a8414acc6b88fda55a2df404eacbf8ecc77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5ff30c3e_156c08e0",
        "filename": "include/core/SkSurfaceProps.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 10586
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-23T00:28:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s it in a nutshell.\n\nI\u0027ve changed it to return a ref, as suggested.  I\u0027ve also made the constructors and `Default` function constexpr.\n\nBut here\u0027s another option:  \n-- Add \"ref\" overloads of all the functions that currently take a pointer.  \n-- Coupled with the default SkSurfaceProps constuctor, the call-sites in Chrome would be clean.\n-- You could deprecate \u0026 remove the pointer variants at your leisure.\n-- Downside: API pollution.",
      "parentUuid": "cf0d8c6d_f4413fe1",
      "revId": "19bf7a8414acc6b88fda55a2df404eacbf8ecc77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fda9e410_f9ddd625",
        "filename": "src/image/SkSurface.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-22T19:57:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Does this produce a static initializer? We\u0027re not really allowed to have any (or at least add any) in Skia. Needs to be constexpr or initialized at runtime.\n\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src.git/+/master/docs/static_initializers.md",
      "revId": "19bf7a8414acc6b88fda55a2df404eacbf8ecc77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3531cdfb_f99f5684",
        "filename": "src/image/SkSurface.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 10586
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-23T00:28:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good to know.\n\nMaking the constructors constexpr eliminates the initializer when build in Chromium w/Clang (even in Debug builds, which surprised me a little).\n\nHowever (!!) I tried some similar code in VC++, and Debug builds still had a static initializer. (Release builds didn\u0027t.)  I don\u0027t know how other compilers might behave.\n\nThe instance *itself* can\u0027t be constexpr since the type is incomplete at the declaration point, so the only other option would be a constexpr-global outside the class.  (In which case we wouldn\u0027t need the \"Default()\" function at all.)\n\nThoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "fda9e410_f9ddd625",
